  1. Go over difference between SRS and Stratified in slides
  • In what situations does Stratification provide a more representative sample?
  • Stratified sampling is especially useful when the cases in each stratum are very similar with respect to the outcome of interest.
  • Allows for minority groups to have a say in the process where they may be missed by SRS
